## Highlights

| Capability                       | Description                                                     |
| -------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **PDB → graph extraction**       | One-line residue contact graph from any PDB, with SASA, surface |
| **9 prediction methods**         | QSVD, DQAW-TimeAvg, DQAW-Lifetime, QPageRank, HeatKernel,       |
|                                  | CommuteTime, GNM, CTQW, supervised MetaLearner                  |
| **QuanAnt colonies**             | Homogeneous, heterogeneous (multi-species), and adaptive        |
| **Pheromone communication**      | Shared trail map biases all ants toward consensus               |
| **APO → HOLO transfer learning** | Learn species reliability on APO, deploy on HOLO                |
| **Voting strategies**            | Argmax, MMR (diversity), RRF, mean / max / weighted             |
| **Parallel execution**           | Thread/process pool with auto-detection                         |
| **Rich visualization**           | Bars, recall curves, species contribution, 3D structures        |

---

## Installation

```bash
pip install quanallo
```

For development:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/quanallo/quanallo.git
cd quanallo
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

Optional — install [Qiskit](https://qiskit.org/) for the actual quantum circuit demos:

```bash
pip install "quanallo[quantum]"
```

---

## Quick start

```python
from quanallo import AllostericPredictor

# Most basic: APO-only prediction with sensible defaults
predictor = AllostericPredictor()
result = predictor.predict_from_pdb(
    apo_pdb="4OBE.pdb",
    auto_active_site_ligand="GDP",  # detect active site near GDP
    top_k=5,
)
print(result.top_residues)        # list of (chain, resnum, resname)
print(result.scores)              # per-residue prediction scores
print(result.method_used)         # 'dqaw_lifetime' (default)

# With HOLO validation
result = predictor.predict_from_pdb(
    apo_pdb="4OBE.pdb",
    holo_pdb="6OIM.pdb",
    auto_active_site_ligand="GDP",
    holo_drug_name="MOV",           # Sotorasib
    top_k=5,
)
print(result.weighted_top5)       # 0–5.0, fuzzy GT credit
print(result.precision_at_k)      # dict[hop_tolerance] -> precision
```

---

## Methods

QuanAllo exposes nine predictor methods, all with the same scoring interface:

### Quantum & quantum-inspired

| Class            | Physics                                                                  |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `QSVD`           | Bottom singular-value subspace of the adjacency matrix                   |
| `DQAWTimeAvg`    | Non-Hermitian continuous-time quantum walk; time-averaged occupation     |
| `DQAWLifetime`   | Slowest eigenmodes of H_eff (longest-lived quantum coherences) ⭐         |
| `QPageRank`      | Personalized PageRank with active site as teleport target                |
| `HeatKernel`     | Heat propagation on the graph from the active site                       |
| `CTQW`           | Standard continuous-time quantum walk                                    |

### Classical

| Class            | Physics                                                                  |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `CommuteTime`    | Inverse effective resistance to the active site                          |
| `GNM`            | Gaussian Network Model: covariance of slow normal modes                  |

### Hybrid

| Class            | Description                                                              |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `MetaLearner`    | Logistic regression on quantum-derived features (trained on APO GT)      |

Use any method standalone:

```python
from quanallo import ProteinGraph
from quanallo.methods import DQAWLifetime

graph = ProteinGraph.from_pdb("4OBE.pdb", auto_active_site_ligand="GDP")
method = DQAWLifetime(alpha=0.4, gamma_absorb=0.2, hop_mu=2.0)
scores = method.compute(graph)
top5 = graph.select_top_k(scores, k=5, mode="mmr")
```

---

## QuanAnt Machines

The flagship feature: **ant colonies of quantum walkers** with pheromone-based
communication. Each ant is a perturbed instance of a method; deposits on its
top-k residues reinforce the pheromone trail; subsequent ants are biased by it.

```python
from quanallo.quanant import QuanAntColony

# Single-species colony (30 DQAW-Lifetime ants)
colony = QuanAntColony(
    species=["dqaw_lifetime"],
    ants_per_species=30,
    n_iter=8,
    parallel=True,
)
result = colony.run(graph)

# Multi-species heterogeneous colony (synergy via shared pheromone)
colony = QuanAntColony(
    species=["qsvd", "dqaw_lifetime", "qpagerank", "heatkernel"],
    ants_per_species=6,
    n_iter=8,
    aggregation="weighted_consensus",
)
result = colony.run(graph)
print(result.top_residues)
print(result.species_contribution)   # which species deposited where
```

### Adaptive QuanAnt (transfer-learn species reliability)

Use APO to learn per-species reliability, then deploy on HOLO with online
adaptive corrections:

```python
from quanallo.quanant import AdaptiveQuanAnt

quanant = AdaptiveQuanAnt(
    species=["qsvd", "dqaw_lifetime", "qpagerank", "heatkernel"],
    ants_per_species=5,
    n_iter=7,
)
quanant.fit(apo_graph)                     # learn species weights on APO
result = quanant.predict(holo_graph)        # deploy on HOLO with online updates
print(result.species_weights_history)       # weight trajectory per iteration
```

---

## API overview

```
quanallo/
├── ProteinGraph              # Core data structure
├── AllostericPredictor       # High-level Predictor (recommended starting point)
├── methods/                  # Individual prediction methods
│   ├── QSVD, DQAWTimeAvg, DQAWLifetime, QPageRank, HeatKernel,
│   ├── CTQW, CommuteTime, GNM, MetaLearner
├── quanant/                  # Ant-colony machines
│   ├── QuanAntColony         # Homo- or heterogeneous colony
│   ├── AdaptiveQuanAnt       # APO→HOLO transfer with adaptive weighting
├── core/                     # Utilities
│   ├── evaluate              # weighted-top-k, precision@k, recall
│   ├── mmr_top_k             # Maximum Marginal Relevance selection
│   ├── rrf_combine           # Reciprocal Rank Fusion
└── visualization/            # Plotting utilities
    ├── plot_scores_3d        # 3D overlay on protein structure
    └── plot_comparison       # Bar / line comparisons across methods
```

